<?xml version="1.0"?>
<fed2-map title='Sigma Space' version='1.00' editor='standard'>

   <location num='2081' flags='slp'>
      <name>Sigma System Interstellar Link</name>
      <desc>The Interstellar link&apos;s beacon blinks to your port side.  Your comms link activates and you recieve the following message, &quot;Welcome to the Sigma Star System, Galaxian space is currently open for the purpose of trade only. Proceed East and dock with Station Galax 1. Please, Do not deviate from course. Thank You!&quot;.</desc>
      <exits e='2082' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

   <location num='2082' flags='sp'>
      <name>Station Galaxia 1 Galaxia Orbit</name>
      <desc>  As you enter this sector you see Station Galax 1 in a stationary postion just outside the gravitational fields of Galaxia and her four moons. The station clearly still under construction is brightly lit, you see spheres of energy swirling around it and moving back and forth between the station and the planets surface.</desc>
      <desc>  Your comms unit activates,  &quot;You are cleared to dock at Docking Bay 3.  All life support systems are operational in the functioning areas of the station. Shuttle service has been established to the Vistors Compound on Galaxia for those with business planetside. Please proceed to Docking Bay 3. Departing ships proceed West to the Interstellar Link.&quot;</desc>
      <exits w='2081' no-exit='moves.noexit.1'/>
   </location>

</fed2-map>

